  "text": "The CSS style change propagation through Chromium's Blink rendering engine follows these key stages:\n\n1. **Style Resolution Stage**: StyleResolver (third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h, line 63) - This class resolves computed styles for DOM elements by matching CSS rules, handling cascades, and applying style adjustments. It is the entry point where CSS selectors are matched against DOM elements to compute the final style.\n\n2. **Layout Tree Stage**: LayoutObject (third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h, line 270) - This is the base class for all layout tree nodes. Each LayoutObject corresponds to a node in the layout tree and encapsulates geometry, positioning, and layout-specific information. The layout tree is built from the DOM tree using the computed styles determined by StyleResolver.\n\n3. **Paint Layer Stage**: PaintLayer (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h, line 174) - PaintLayer is a key abstraction that handles complex painting operations including opacity, clipping, filters, reflections, and hardware acceleration. It organizes the layout tree into a hierarchical paint tree structure for rendering.\n\n4. **Display List Recording Stage**: PaintController (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h, line 131) and DisplayItemList (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h, line 28) - PaintController is responsible for recording paint operations as display items into a DisplayItemList. This display list represents the low-level drawing operations needed to render the visual output.\n\nThe pipeline flows: CSS styles (StyleResolver) → Layout objects (LayoutObject) → Paint layers (PaintLayer) → Display items (PaintController/DisplayItemList) → Rasterization."
}

